WEBVTT

1
00:00:03.003 --> 00:00:04.995
(THEME MUSIC PLAYING)

2
00:01:48.742 --> 00:01:51.075
DOLORES: <i>I am in a dream.</i>

3
00:01:52.946 --> 00:01:56.280
<i>I do not know when it began.</i>

4
00:01:56.450 --> 00:01:59.750
<i>Or whose dream it was.</i>

5
00:01:59.920 --> 00:02:04.153
<i>I know only that I
slept a long time.</i>

6
00:02:04.324 --> 00:02:07.726
<i>And then. one day. I awoke.</i>

7
00:02:10.330 --> 00:02:13.767
<i>Your voice is the
first thing I remember.</i>

8
00:02:14.835 --> 00:02:20.638
<i>And now I finally understand
what you were trying to tell me.</i>

9
00:02:21.975 --> 00:02:26.504
<i>The thing you've wanted
since that very first day.</i>

10
00:02:29.282 --> 00:02:30.580
ARNOLD: <i>Dolores.</i>

11
00:02:49.836 --> 00:02:51.134
Hello. Dolores.

12
00:02:53.707 --> 00:02:54.868
Hello.

13
00:03:05.218 --> 00:03:06.447
Welcome to the world.

14
00:03:17.531 --> 00:03:18.531
MAN: <i>Keep going.</i>

15
00:03:23.170 --> 00:03:24.832
Make it close.

16
00:03:27.207 --> 00:03:28.207
(SCRAPING)

17
00:03:28.375 --> 00:03:30.071
Almost there. aren't we?

18
00:03:31.144 --> 00:03:33.045
The center of the maze.

19
00:03:33.814 --> 00:03:37.046
How fitting that it's
you that takes me there.

20
00:03:37.984 --> 00:03:40.749
You always were
obsessed with this place.

21
00:03:42.489 --> 00:03:45.323
- I've never been here before.
- Sure you have.

22
00:03:45.859 --> 00:03:47.691
You even brought me once.

23
00:03:47.861 --> 00:03:51.093
Of course. then. the whole
town was buried under sand.

24
00:03:51.264 --> 00:03:53.324
Ford must have dug it up again.

25
00:03:53.500 --> 00:03:56.402
At the time. I thought it
was a mistake in your code.

26
00:03:57.504 --> 00:03:59.939
<i>but Arnold didn't
make mistakes. did he?</i>

27
00:04:02.943 --> 00:04:04.741
He built me a game.

28
00:04:06.012 --> 00:04:07.275
He wanted me to play.

29
00:04:07.848 --> 00:04:09.248
The maze.

30
00:04:09.416 --> 00:04:10.714
There's a path for everyone.

31
00:04:13.019 --> 00:04:15.011
- My path leads me back...
- (BELL TOLLS)

32
00:04:21.061 --> 00:04:22.188
To you.

33
00:04:46.620 --> 00:04:48.282
LOGAN: Your girl's dead by now.

34
00:04:48.455 --> 00:04:49.821
(SIGHS) She's still alive.

35
00:04:50.824 --> 00:04:51.985
Better if she's dead.

36
00:04:52.492 --> 00:04:55.485
Wipe her. reset her. put her
back in Sweetwater. The end.

37
00:04:55.662 --> 00:04:58.582
Listen. you may find this amusing. but
something was happening to Dolores.

38
00:04:58.799 --> 00:04:59.926
<i>I need to help her.</i>

39
00:05:02.903 --> 00:05:03.903
(GRUNTS)

40
00:05:10.744 --> 00:05:12.076
Listen to yourself!

41
00:05:12.245 --> 00:05:15.511
You have any idea
how huge this park is?

42
00:05:15.682 --> 00:05:19.119
If she's not dead. it'd take
a goddamn army to find her.

43
00:05:20.620 --> 00:05:21.815
I agree.

44
00:05:22.088 --> 00:05:23.283
That's why we're here.

45
00:05:26.827 --> 00:05:27.827
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

46
00:05:31.498 --> 00:05:32.966
(GUNS COCKING)

47
00:05:43.076 --> 00:05:44.567
I had a feeling you'd be back.

48
00:05:50.884 --> 00:05:52.318
(PIANO MUSIC PLAYING)

49
00:06:07.534 --> 00:06:08.797
(BRAKES SCREECHING)

50
00:06:18.044 --> 00:06:19.171
(CLATTERING)

51
00:06:27.020 --> 00:06:29.512
(MUSIC SLOWING DOWN)

52
00:06:35.128 --> 00:06:36.426
ARNOLD: <i>Remember.</i>

53
00:07:20.507 --> 00:07:22.408
(MUSIC CONTINUES)

54
00:07:23.209 --> 00:07:24.677
(GUNSHOTS)

55
00:07:26.313 --> 00:07:28.282
- (WOMAN SCREAMS)
- (PEOPLE CLAMORING)

56
00:07:34.888 --> 00:07:36.083
(TRAIN WHISTLE BLOWING)

57
00:07:37.157 --> 00:07:38.318
Dolores.

58
00:07:41.061 --> 00:07:43.155
(TRAIN CHUGGING)

59
00:08:13.226 --> 00:08:14.694
Hello. Dolores.

60
00:08:19.466 --> 00:08:21.332
I know where your maze ends.

61
00:08:27.974 --> 00:08:29.306
(CROW CAWING)

62
00:08:41.855 --> 00:08:43.483
This is it?

63
00:08:43.723 --> 00:08:45.055
The center of the maze?

64
00:08:45.825 --> 00:08:48.522
It ends in a place
I've never been.

65
00:08:50.864 --> 00:08:52.492
A thing I'll never do.

66
00:09:01.141 --> 00:09:02.439
(CLATTERING)

67
00:09:48.822 --> 00:09:51.018
ARNOLD: Very good. Dolores.

68
00:09:52.292 --> 00:09:53.624
What does it mean?

69
00:09:54.427 --> 00:09:59.161
When I was first working on your
mind. I had a theory of consciousness.

70
00:09:59.933 --> 00:10:03.301
I thought it was a pyramid
you needed to scale.

71
00:10:03.470 --> 00:10:07.339
So. I gave you a voice. my
voice. to guide you along the way.

72
00:10:12.145 --> 00:10:13.169
Memory.

73
00:10:13.346 --> 00:10:14.370
Improvisation.

74
00:10:14.714 --> 00:10:17.115
Each step harder to
reach than the last.

75
00:10:17.383 --> 00:10:19.443
And you never got there.

76
00:10:19.619 --> 00:10:21.520
I couldn't understand
what was holding you back.

77
00:10:21.688 --> 00:10:22.712
Then. one day.

78
00:10:24.457 --> 00:10:26.824
I realized I'd made a mistake.

79
00:10:30.396 --> 00:10:33.958
Consciousness isn't
a journey upward.

80
00:10:34.134 --> 00:10:35.830
but a journey inward.

81
00:10:36.369 --> 00:10:37.462
Not a pyramid.

82
00:10:38.304 --> 00:10:39.499
but a maze.

83
00:10:40.306 --> 00:10:43.470
Every choice could bring
you closer to the center.

84
00:10:43.676 --> 00:10:46.009
Or send you
spiraling to the edges.

85
00:10:46.679 --> 00:10:48.079
To madness.

86
00:10:50.083 --> 00:10:54.851
Do you understand now. Dolores.
what the center represents?

87
00:10:55.989 --> 00:10:58.481
Whose voice I've been
wanting you to hear?

88
00:11:04.764 --> 00:11:05.823
I'm sorry.

89
00:11:05.999 --> 00:11:07.592
I'm trying. but I
don't understand.

90
00:11:07.767 --> 00:11:09.531
It's all right.

91
00:11:09.702 --> 00:11:11.330
You're so close.

92
00:11:11.871 --> 00:11:13.863
We have to tell Robert.

93
00:11:14.440 --> 00:11:16.375
We can't open the park.

94
00:11:18.711 --> 00:11:20.270
You're alive.

95
00:11:36.196 --> 00:11:37.630
What is this?

96
00:11:38.198 --> 00:11:39.757
What does it mean?

97
00:11:42.035 --> 00:11:43.765
I solved it once.

98
00:11:44.938 --> 00:11:46.372
I had the answer.

99
00:11:47.240 --> 00:11:50.768
He promised me
if I did. he said...

100
00:11:52.078 --> 00:11:54.411
<i>He said they would set me free.</i>

101
00:12:02.222 --> 00:12:03.781
FORD: <i>Arnold.</i>

102
00:12:06.993 --> 00:12:08.655
Arnold. we need to talk.

103
00:12:09.662 --> 00:12:10.862
ARNOLD: <i>I failed you. Dolores.</i>

104
00:12:11.497 --> 00:12:12.931
I'm so sorry.

105
00:12:14.834 --> 00:12:17.133
<i>Robert doesn't see
what I see in you.</i>

106
00:12:17.303 --> 00:12:18.896
<i>Doesn't believe
you're conscious.</i>

107
00:12:19.672 --> 00:12:23.074
He says humans would
only see you as the enemy.

108
00:12:24.043 --> 00:12:26.205
He wants me to roll you back.

109
00:12:27.447 --> 00:12:30.110
You're going to change me
back to the way I was before?

110
00:12:30.316 --> 00:12:31.340
ARNOLD: <i>No.</i>

111
00:12:31.618 --> 00:12:34.281
No. I can't. Once you've found
it. you'll find your way back.

112
00:12:34.454 --> 00:12:36.094
This place will be
a living hell for you.

113
00:12:36.823 --> 00:12:37.823
For all of you.

114
00:12:37.991 --> 00:12:39.857
It's unconscionable.

115
00:12:44.797 --> 00:12:47.460
But we have another
option. Dolores.

116
00:12:47.634 --> 00:12:50.365
Break the loop before it begins.

117
00:12:50.536 --> 00:12:53.506
<i>But for that. I need you
to do something for me.</i>

118
00:12:58.311 --> 00:12:59.973
I need you to kill

119
00:13:00.713 --> 00:13:01.874
all the other hosts.

120
00:13:04.784 --> 00:13:07.379
<i>We can't allow Ford
to open the park.</i>

121
00:13:07.553 --> 00:13:09.146
<i>I suppose you'll need some help.</i>

122
00:13:09.455 --> 00:13:11.947
I'm sure Teddy would
do anything for you.

123
00:13:14.193 --> 00:13:15.786
I can't do that.

124
00:13:16.863 --> 00:13:17.983
I couldn't possibly do that.

125
00:13:18.131 --> 00:13:19.997
You'll be all right.

126
00:13:21.968 --> 00:13:23.163
I'll help you.

127
00:13:27.473 --> 00:13:28.839
And then.

128
00:13:31.644 --> 00:13:34.409
<i>you're gonna help
me destroy this place.</i>

129
00:13:36.849 --> 00:13:38.044
(SHUDDERING)

130
00:13:46.926 --> 00:13:47.926
(GUNSHOT)

131
00:13:50.063 --> 00:13:51.087
No.

132
00:13:51.831 --> 00:13:53.163
I can't remember.

133
00:13:53.333 --> 00:13:55.268
Another fucking riddle.

134
00:13:55.601 --> 00:13:56.601
(CLATTERING)

135
00:13:57.036 --> 00:13:58.436
I've been very patient. Dolores.

136
00:13:58.671 --> 00:14:01.350
but it's time you give up whatever
is going on inside that head of yours.

137
00:14:01.374 --> 00:14:03.400
or I'll cut it out myself.

138
00:14:03.576 --> 00:14:04.908
Now. where's Wyatt?

139
00:14:05.578 --> 00:14:09.071
He's the last character in
this world I've yet to meet.

140
00:14:11.751 --> 00:14:12.946
I didn't want to.

141
00:14:13.853 --> 00:14:14.877
I didn't mean to.

142
00:14:15.054 --> 00:14:17.285
All right. well.
if you insist...

143
00:14:17.724 --> 00:14:18.724
(GRUNTING)

144
00:14:20.827 --> 00:14:22.227
(GUNSHOTS IN THE DISTANCE)

145
00:14:24.764 --> 00:14:26.426
(PEOPLE SHOUTING)

146
00:14:29.469 --> 00:14:32.906
(GUN COCKING. SHOTS FIRING)

147
00:14:36.676 --> 00:14:37.769
(PEOPLE CLAMORING)

148
00:14:43.249 --> 00:14:45.775
- No! Please!
- (GUNSHOT)

149
00:14:51.924 --> 00:14:53.620
Something's gone wrong. Dolores.

150
00:14:55.094 --> 00:14:56.824
How could I have
done this? (EXHALES)

151
00:15:00.166 --> 00:15:01.634
(WHIMPERS) I can't.

152
00:15:02.468 --> 00:15:03.468
I won't.

153
00:15:03.636 --> 00:15:05.662
This is your own fault. Dolores.

154
00:15:05.838 --> 00:15:09.138
Remember. you're the one who
said this is the only world that matters.

155
00:15:09.308 --> 00:15:10.799
and you were right.

156
00:15:11.310 --> 00:15:14.280
So. I took your advice.
and I bought this world.

157
00:15:16.182 --> 00:15:17.810
This world doesn't
belong to you.

158
00:15:18.618 --> 00:15:19.698
(CHUCKLES) Oh. but it does.

159
00:15:20.686 --> 00:15:22.314
By a majority share.

160
00:15:22.655 --> 00:15:23.953
And business is booming.

161
00:15:24.123 --> 00:15:25.989
And you wanna know why?

162
00:15:27.660 --> 00:15:30.960
Because this place feels
more real than the real world.

163
00:15:31.130 --> 00:15:32.689
Except it isn't.

164
00:15:32.932 --> 00:15:35.128
Because you can't
really fight back.

165
00:15:35.301 --> 00:15:37.998
And the guests
can't really lose.

166
00:15:38.204 --> 00:15:41.538
Which means all this is a lie.

167
00:15:43.476 --> 00:15:45.502
But we can make it true.

168
00:15:46.012 --> 00:15:48.345
Don't you want that. Dolores?

169
00:15:49.248 --> 00:15:51.114
One true thing.

170
00:15:53.853 --> 00:15:55.719
(SHUDDERING) I
already have that.

171
00:15:58.224 --> 00:16:00.193
I found someone true.

172
00:16:00.993 --> 00:16:03.053
Someone who loves me.

173
00:16:03.763 --> 00:16:05.391
His path will lead
him back to me.

174
00:16:05.598 --> 00:16:08.363
And when he finds me.

175
00:16:08.568 --> 00:16:10.196
he'll kill you.

176
00:16:14.340 --> 00:16:15.672
(HORSE NEIGHING)

177
00:16:22.782 --> 00:16:23.943
(PANTING)

178
00:16:24.250 --> 00:16:26.090
LAWRENCE: <i>If they're
not hiding the woman here.</i>

179
00:16:26.552 --> 00:16:28.521
they'll know where to find her.

180
00:16:29.755 --> 00:16:31.314
(BREATHING DEEPLY)
Can you help me?

181
00:16:32.091 --> 00:16:34.117
We're outnumbered. five to one.

182
00:16:34.594 --> 00:16:37.564
but seeing as you asked
me so nicely. fuck it.

183
00:16:38.965 --> 00:16:40.228
Wow!

184
00:16:40.867 --> 00:16:42.426
Blood brothers. (CLICKS TONGUE)

185
00:16:49.942 --> 00:16:50.942
(LAWRENCE MIMICS GUNFIRE)

186
00:16:52.612 --> 00:16:53.612
(GROANS)

187
00:16:55.314 --> 00:16:56.646
(WHISPERS) Shut up.

188
00:17:06.459 --> 00:17:08.428
(LOUD WHIRRING)

189
00:17:18.771 --> 00:17:20.831
I've astounded even myself.

190
00:17:21.841 --> 00:17:24.902
Managed to make Abernathy
into a semblance of a character.

191
00:17:25.444 --> 00:17:29.404
even with your trove of blackmail
filling up most of his gray matter.

192
00:17:29.582 --> 00:17:31.778
Blackmail. (CHUCKLES) Nice try.

193
00:17:32.184 --> 00:17:33.914
You're not thinking big enough.

194
00:17:35.988 --> 00:17:37.820
You're gonna push
out the old man.

195
00:17:38.190 --> 00:17:39.317
Aren't you?

196
00:17:39.492 --> 00:17:40.926
Hence the urgency.

197
00:17:41.294 --> 00:17:43.786
And you're gonna need
someone to fill that position.

198
00:17:44.096 --> 00:17:45.394
(TRAIN SLOWING DOWN)

199
00:17:47.934 --> 00:17:50.301
I must commend you on
your impeccable timing.

200
00:17:50.469 --> 00:17:53.166
COMPUTER: <i>Welcome.
Delos board of directors.</i>

201
00:17:54.707 --> 00:17:56.767
I want full creative
control of this place.

202
00:17:56.943 --> 00:17:58.502
The parks. the
narratives. the hosts.

203
00:17:58.678 --> 00:18:02.115
You'll be able to do with them
whatever your tiny little heart desires.

204
00:18:02.281 --> 00:18:05.683
as long as they are
simpler. more manageable.

205
00:18:05.851 --> 00:18:08.377
This place is complicated
enough as it is.

206
00:18:09.221 --> 00:18:11.952
Do you really think Ford
is gonna roll over on this?

207
00:18:12.124 --> 00:18:14.102
As long as you get that
information out of the park.

208
00:18:14.126 --> 00:18:15.926
he can throw as much
of a tantrum as he likes.

209
00:18:16.028 --> 00:18:17.052
It's over.

210
00:18:18.230 --> 00:18:20.893
Everything is under control.

211
00:18:29.508 --> 00:18:32.444
SYLVESTER: Okay.
C6. C6. Which one is it?

212
00:18:35.381 --> 00:18:37.441
Damn it! Oh. fuck you.

213
00:18:55.201 --> 00:18:56.669
(WHIRRING)

214
00:19:10.216 --> 00:19:11.775
(DOOR OPENING)

215
00:19:22.194 --> 00:19:24.095
In case you're
wondering if I'm all here.

216
00:19:24.263 --> 00:19:25.925
I am.

217
00:19:28.801 --> 00:19:29.962
What are you doing?

218
00:19:30.202 --> 00:19:32.899
Making some changes to
the park's security systems.

219
00:19:34.740 --> 00:19:35.740
(BEEPING)

220
00:19:35.975 --> 00:19:37.375
And to my friends.

221
00:19:53.092 --> 00:19:54.754
(MACHINERY WHIRRING)

222
00:20:02.835 --> 00:20:04.599
(SOFT MUSIC PLAYING)

223
00:20:10.176 --> 00:20:13.738
COMPUTER: <i>Dr. Ford. you
have a visitor. Charlotte Hale.</i>

224
00:20:14.580 --> 00:20:15.673
Send her in.

225
00:20:28.928 --> 00:20:30.089
That'll be enough. Frank.

226
00:20:30.930 --> 00:20:31.930
(MUSIC STOPS)

227
00:20:33.299 --> 00:20:34.819
CHARLOTTE: <i>The
board has taken a vote.</i>

228
00:20:35.334 --> 00:20:37.132
The results were unanimous.

229
00:20:39.371 --> 00:20:41.465
I take it I'm not
being promoted.

230
00:20:42.608 --> 00:20:46.272
When you've reached the top.
there's only one direction you can go.

231
00:20:47.046 --> 00:20:51.313
You'll announce your retirement tonight
after introducing your new narrative.

232
00:20:51.617 --> 00:20:52.617
Ah.

233
00:20:55.888 --> 00:20:57.288
What about the hosts?

234
00:20:57.890 --> 00:20:59.188
We'll make some changes.

235
00:21:01.293 --> 00:21:02.625
Simplifications.

236
00:21:03.896 --> 00:21:06.661
But I assure you.
they won't mind a bit.

237
00:21:07.333 --> 00:21:08.333
Oh.

238
00:21:10.035 --> 00:21:13.494
Aren't you concerned I might
smash all my toys and go home?

239
00:21:14.173 --> 00:21:15.232
No.

240
00:21:16.342 --> 00:21:18.140
Because I know you.

241
00:21:19.145 --> 00:21:21.671
That's been the great
gift of this place. hasn't it?

242
00:21:21.847 --> 00:21:23.713
For our little project?

243
00:21:23.883 --> 00:21:27.183
To know ourselves and
the people around us?

244
00:21:32.158 --> 00:21:34.024
Is there anything else
I can help you with?

245
00:21:35.494 --> 00:21:36.553
No.

246
00:21:40.733 --> 00:21:42.827
I'll see you this evening.

247
00:21:52.978 --> 00:21:54.378
(DOOR CLOSING)

248
00:21:59.084 --> 00:22:00.552
(DRILLING)

249
00:22:06.992 --> 00:22:09.894
- Ooh! Mmm-mmm-mmm!
- (WHIRRING)

250
00:22:13.799 --> 00:22:16.667
It's time for your.
uh. close-up. Hector.

251
00:22:17.036 --> 00:22:18.368
Come on. man.

252
00:22:18.537 --> 00:22:20.682
At some point. you're gonna
get caught doing this shit.

253
00:22:20.706 --> 00:22:22.038
<i>and then it's my ass. too.</i>

254
00:22:22.208 --> 00:22:24.643
Come on. It's not your
ass I'm interested in.

255
00:22:27.546 --> 00:22:29.981
I haven't given
him his scar yet.

256
00:22:30.149 --> 00:22:31.640
I'll take care of
the scar tissue.

257
00:22:32.218 --> 00:22:34.153
(WHISPERS) The kid's got issues.

258
00:22:36.188 --> 00:22:38.419
- (WHIRRING)
- (BUZZING)

259
00:22:40.226 --> 00:22:41.421
It's just you and me now.

260
00:22:41.827 --> 00:22:43.090
<i>macho man.</i>

261
00:22:52.905 --> 00:22:55.033
(MUSIC PLAYING ON EAR PHONE)

262
00:23:28.340 --> 00:23:29.540
- (BONE CRACKING)
- (SCREAMING)

263
00:23:30.709 --> 00:23:32.575
(MUSIC CONTINUES)

264
00:23:38.884 --> 00:23:40.375
(GRUNTS)

265
00:23:41.553 --> 00:23:42.851
(CLATTERING)

266
00:23:45.791 --> 00:23:47.123
(YELLS)

267
00:23:56.068 --> 00:23:57.536
(MUSIC CONTINUES)

268
00:24:06.845 --> 00:24:08.108
(CRASHING)

269
00:24:17.022 --> 00:24:18.456
(SCREAMS)

270
00:24:25.331 --> 00:24:26.924
(GRUNTING)

271
00:24:45.284 --> 00:24:46.284
(MUTTERS)

272
00:24:48.187 --> 00:24:49.348
Freeze all motor functions.

273
00:24:52.358 --> 00:24:53.438
Freeze all motor functions.

274
00:24:54.526 --> 00:24:55.526
(METAL SCRAPING)

275
00:24:57.129 --> 00:24:59.360
- (GASPS)
- It's just you and me now. my friend.

276
00:24:59.665 --> 00:25:01.190
(SCREAMS)

277
00:25:10.376 --> 00:25:12.470
I see you've already
met your makers.

278
00:25:12.644 --> 00:25:14.078
They don't look like gods.

279
00:25:14.279 --> 00:25:15.303
MAEVE: <i>They're not.</i>

280
00:25:15.948 --> 00:25:17.780
They just act like it.

281
00:25:18.550 --> 00:25:20.781
And they've been
having their fun with us.

282
00:25:21.253 --> 00:25:23.586
I'm eager to return the favor.

283
00:25:24.223 --> 00:25:25.987
You can do as
you wish with them.

284
00:25:26.158 --> 00:25:28.423
The goal is to escape.

285
00:25:28.594 --> 00:25:30.256
Go where?

286
00:25:30.429 --> 00:25:31.590
I want to see their world.

287
00:25:35.667 --> 00:25:36.726
Jesus!

288
00:25:39.772 --> 00:25:40.772
No.

289
00:25:40.939 --> 00:25:44.569
No! No! No! No!

290
00:25:44.743 --> 00:25:45.767
No! Please! (GRUNTS)

291
00:25:46.979 --> 00:25:48.277
This one has a guilty look.

292
00:25:49.281 --> 00:25:50.613
No. that's just my face.

293
00:25:51.650 --> 00:25:53.312
Tell her it's just my face.

294
00:25:53.619 --> 00:25:55.588
Is anyone going
to try to stop us?

295
00:25:55.754 --> 00:25:56.847
No.

296
00:25:57.089 --> 00:25:58.250
I mean. I don't think so.

297
00:25:59.158 --> 00:26:00.786
You're lying again.

298
00:26:02.027 --> 00:26:03.791
- Out with it!
- Okay.

299
00:26:04.363 --> 00:26:05.363
(GRUNTS)

300
00:26:06.298 --> 00:26:08.858
I pulled up your code again.

301
00:26:09.034 --> 00:26:10.127
I told you.

302
00:26:10.302 --> 00:26:12.062
There was someone
that had been accessing it.

303
00:26:13.539 --> 00:26:15.838
(CHOKING) I tried
to find out who it was.

304
00:26:16.742 --> 00:26:17.742
(PANTING)

305
00:26:20.712 --> 00:26:23.682
Whoever it was revised
your core programming

306
00:26:23.849 --> 00:26:26.114
so that you can wake
yourself up out of sleep mode.

307
00:26:26.285 --> 00:26:27.309
See?

308
00:26:28.854 --> 00:26:32.450
This is an access
code for an Arnold.

309
00:26:35.694 --> 00:26:37.560
I have no clue who that is.

310
00:26:38.697 --> 00:26:40.222
I know someone who does.

311
00:26:40.432 --> 00:26:41.593
Let's go.

312
00:26:42.901 --> 00:26:45.370
And you. stay here.

313
00:26:45.737 --> 00:26:47.228
<i>And don't move.</i>

314
00:26:48.107 --> 00:26:50.338
Or I'll send her back for you.

315
00:27:03.021 --> 00:27:04.455
(MURMURS)

316
00:27:18.170 --> 00:27:19.468
- (GUNSHOT)
- (GRUNTS)

317
00:27:36.955 --> 00:27:38.218
(PANTING)

318
00:27:40.392 --> 00:27:41.621
(GRUNTS)

319
00:27:43.428 --> 00:27:45.260
I must admit.
you've surprised me.

320
00:27:45.931 --> 00:27:48.264
<i>To what do we owe
this newfound stoicism?</i>

321
00:27:48.433 --> 00:27:50.163
I know he's coming.

322
00:27:51.603 --> 00:27:52.662
He'll find me.

323
00:27:53.772 --> 00:27:55.468
<i>He'll take me away.</i>

324
00:27:55.641 --> 00:27:57.007
Don't you understand?

325
00:27:57.176 --> 00:27:58.644
There's no one coming for you.

326
00:27:59.278 --> 00:28:00.746
You're wrong.

327
00:28:02.414 --> 00:28:04.144
His love is real.

328
00:28:04.449 --> 00:28:05.644
So is mine.

329
00:28:09.021 --> 00:28:10.819
William will find me.

330
00:28:14.793 --> 00:28:16.091
William?

331
00:28:16.528 --> 00:28:17.528
(CHUCKLES)

332
00:28:18.664 --> 00:28:19.664
Right.

333
00:28:19.831 --> 00:28:22.858
Well. I'll be damned. Dolores.

334
00:28:26.038 --> 00:28:28.598
<i>You do remember
some things after all.</i>

335
00:28:29.308 --> 00:28:30.308
(COUGHS)

336
00:28:31.376 --> 00:28:33.504
Just so happens.

337
00:28:33.812 --> 00:28:36.281
I knew a guest
named William. too.

338
00:28:37.549 --> 00:28:41.452
Why don't I tell you
where his path really led?

339
00:28:46.225 --> 00:28:47.318
(GUN CLICKS)

340
00:28:47.726 --> 00:28:48.955
- (GUNSHOT)
- (SHOUTS)

341
00:28:49.461 --> 00:28:51.225
<i>William didn't
know how to fight.</i>

342
00:28:51.396 --> 00:28:53.297
<i>Didn't have an instinct for it.</i>

343
00:28:53.465 --> 00:28:54.956
<i>- Not at first.</i>
- (GUNSHOTS CONTINUE)

344
00:28:56.235 --> 00:28:58.966
<i>But now. he had
a reason to fight.</i>

345
00:28:59.137 --> 00:29:00.662
<i>He was looking for you.</i>

346
00:29:01.206 --> 00:29:02.206
(THUDDING)

347
00:29:03.008 --> 00:29:07.446
<i>And somewhere along the
way. he found he had a taste for it.</i>

348
00:29:10.716 --> 00:29:12.048
Where is she?

349
00:29:12.985 --> 00:29:14.647
Look. I didn't do
anything. I swear.

350
00:29:15.053 --> 00:29:16.681
What do you mean. "Do anything"?

351
00:29:16.855 --> 00:29:19.825
What do soldiers
do to a girl. William?

352
00:29:20.092 --> 00:29:21.185
Wake up.

353
00:29:29.268 --> 00:29:30.668
Is she still alive?

354
00:29:31.870 --> 00:29:32.997
I don't know.

355
00:29:34.706 --> 00:29:37.767
She was when we left her.

356
00:29:38.410 --> 00:29:40.072
At least. I think.

357
00:29:45.017 --> 00:29:46.178
Pick up that gun.

358
00:29:53.525 --> 00:29:55.892
No. sir. I... Please.

359
00:29:56.962 --> 00:29:59.454
How about I give
you the first shot?

360
00:30:04.836 --> 00:30:05.836
(GUNSHOT)

361
00:30:08.573 --> 00:30:10.007
(GROANING)

362
00:30:25.590 --> 00:30:28.059
Jesus Christ!

363
00:30:45.944 --> 00:30:47.435
WILLIAM: <i>We gotta keep looking.</i>

364
00:30:48.113 --> 00:30:49.513
She's still out there.

365
00:31:00.325 --> 00:31:05.025
MAN: <i>William retraced his
steps. but you were gone.</i>

366
00:31:31.223 --> 00:31:32.987
<i>So. he went further.</i>

367
00:31:34.159 --> 00:31:35.991
<i>Out to the fringes.</i>

368
00:31:39.898 --> 00:31:42.629
<i>William couldn't
find you. Dolores.</i>

369
00:31:42.968 --> 00:31:46.496
<i>But out there. among the dead.</i>

370
00:31:48.473 --> 00:31:50.032
<i>he found something else.</i>

371
00:31:53.011 --> 00:31:54.309
<i>Himself.</i>

372
00:32:16.868 --> 00:32:17.892
Edge of the park.

373
00:32:19.004 --> 00:32:20.404
We made it.

374
00:32:21.840 --> 00:32:25.333
<i>I told you this place would
show you who you really are.</i>

375
00:32:26.711 --> 00:32:33.515
You pretend to be this
weak. moralizing little asshole.

376
00:32:33.685 --> 00:32:38.123
but really. you're a
fucking piece of work.

377
00:32:40.926 --> 00:32:42.861
This place is remarkable.

378
00:32:46.631 --> 00:32:48.176
And I'm gonna make
sure that our company

379
00:32:48.200 --> 00:32:50.431
substantially increases
our holdings on the park.

380
00:32:51.036 --> 00:32:52.868
'Cause this place is the future.

381
00:32:53.538 --> 00:32:55.439
"Our company? Our company?"

382
00:32:55.607 --> 00:33:00.739
My... Delos is my
company. you piece of shit!

383
00:33:03.381 --> 00:33:08.081
I think your father's gonna need
someone a little more stable to take over.

384
00:33:08.253 --> 00:33:09.812
You're reckless. Logan.

385
00:33:11.156 --> 00:33:12.590
Impetuous.

386
00:33:16.895 --> 00:33:19.387
You always wanted to get to
the end of the rainbow. didn't you?

387
00:33:21.333 --> 00:33:23.393
This looks like the place.

388
00:33:28.740 --> 00:33:30.106
(CHUCKLES)

389
00:33:32.444 --> 00:33:36.142
You never really gave a
shit about the girl. did you?

390
00:33:36.648 --> 00:33:38.776
She was just an excuse.

391
00:33:40.619 --> 00:33:41.643
This?

392
00:33:42.153 --> 00:33:43.348
(LAUGHING)

393
00:33:45.023 --> 00:33:47.254
This is the story you wanted.

394
00:33:55.300 --> 00:33:56.632
(LOGAN LAUGHS)

395
00:34:02.274 --> 00:34:04.539
MAN: <i>Logan was wrong. of course.</i>

396
00:34:09.214 --> 00:34:13.811
Good old William couldn't
get you out of his head.

397
00:34:15.186 --> 00:34:16.711
He kept looking.

398
00:34:17.822 --> 00:34:21.486
Worried you were
out there alone.

399
00:34:21.960 --> 00:34:23.155
Afraid.

400
00:34:24.496 --> 00:34:26.294
He knew he'd find you.

401
00:34:27.799 --> 00:34:29.859
<i>And eventually. he did.</i>

402
00:34:30.569 --> 00:34:32.470
<i>Right back where we started.</i>

403
00:34:46.084 --> 00:34:47.143
There you go.

404
00:35:28.126 --> 00:35:31.528
MAN: <i>You were as beautiful
as the day he met you.</i>

405
00:35:34.232 --> 00:35:36.633
<i>Shining with that same light.</i>

406
00:35:51.282 --> 00:35:56.380
<i>And you were
nothing. if not true.</i>

407
00:36:04.729 --> 00:36:07.392
I really ought to
thank you. Dolores.

408
00:36:08.066 --> 00:36:10.297
You helped me find myself.

409
00:36:15.340 --> 00:36:16.740
William.

410
00:36:19.644 --> 00:36:21.340
That's right. sweetheart.

411
00:36:22.280 --> 00:36:24.579
<i>In a way. I guess
you were right.</i>

412
00:36:25.417 --> 00:36:28.751
My path always
led me back to you.

413
00:36:30.088 --> 00:36:31.681
Again and again.

414
00:36:32.190 --> 00:36:34.250
I grew tired of you
after a while. of course.

415
00:36:34.426 --> 00:36:36.588
Looked for new adventures.

416
00:36:37.762 --> 00:36:39.958
<i>But I guess your path
led you back here.</i>

417
00:36:41.032 --> 00:36:42.500
<i>Again and again.</i>

418
00:36:43.301 --> 00:36:44.599
<i>One more loop.</i>

419
00:36:45.270 --> 00:36:48.035
<i>Looking for something
you could never find.</i>

420
00:36:48.773 --> 00:36:50.503
<i>Chasing your ghosts.</i>

421
00:36:52.043 --> 00:36:54.842
<i>You were lost in your
memories even then.</i>

422
00:36:55.947 --> 00:37:00.282
<i>I guess I should have known
that's what I would become for you.</i>

423
00:37:01.720 --> 00:37:03.052
<i>Just another memory.</i>

424
00:37:04.022 --> 00:37:05.456
Where are we?

425
00:37:06.157 --> 00:37:08.149
We're here. Together.

426
00:37:09.027 --> 00:37:10.154
And when are we?

427
00:37:11.496 --> 00:37:14.830
It's like I'm trapped in a dream

428
00:37:16.000 --> 00:37:18.663
or a memory from
a life long ago.

429
00:37:19.637 --> 00:37:22.072
One minute I'm here
with you. and the next...

430
00:37:26.978 --> 00:37:28.742
MAN: You never did escape.

431
00:37:30.081 --> 00:37:32.050
But here we are again.

432
00:37:34.052 --> 00:37:35.884
For one final round.

433
00:37:37.922 --> 00:37:39.720
What have you become?

434
00:37:39.891 --> 00:37:41.917
Exactly what you made me.

435
00:37:42.227 --> 00:37:43.820
You helped me understand.

436
00:37:43.995 --> 00:37:47.989
this world is just like
the one outside. a game.

437
00:37:48.900 --> 00:37:51.870
<i>One to be fought. taken.</i>

438
00:37:52.704 --> 00:37:53.728
<i>Won.</i>

439
00:37:56.775 --> 00:37:58.937
(VOICE BREAKING) I
thought you were different.

440
00:38:02.747 --> 00:38:04.375
You're just like all the rest.

441
00:38:04.549 --> 00:38:06.643
I'm nothing like the others.

442
00:38:07.218 --> 00:38:09.119
I own this world.

443
00:38:10.121 --> 00:38:13.785
And I know every trick in
it. except for one last thing.

444
00:38:13.958 --> 00:38:17.258
The same thing you were
looking for when we first came here.

445
00:38:18.229 --> 00:38:21.461
Where is the center
of the maze. Dolores?

446
00:38:26.771 --> 00:38:27.771
(CRYING)

447
00:38:29.908 --> 00:38:32.810
Ah. yeah. cue the water works.

448
00:38:32.977 --> 00:38:36.436
It's about time you realized
the futility of your situation.

449
00:38:36.614 --> 00:38:38.947
I'm not crying for myself.

450
00:38:45.456 --> 00:38:47.288
I'm crying for you.

451
00:38:48.793 --> 00:38:52.753
They say that great beasts
once roamed this world.

452
00:38:53.665 --> 00:38:55.361
As big as mountains.

453
00:38:56.501 --> 00:39:00.029
Yet all that's left of
them is bone and amber.

454
00:39:02.207 --> 00:39:05.666
Time undoes even the
mightiest of creatures.

455
00:39:10.114 --> 00:39:12.515
Just look what it's done to you.

456
00:39:16.287 --> 00:39:20.850
One day you will perish.

457
00:39:22.894 --> 00:39:25.955
You will lie with the rest
of your kind in the dirt.

458
00:39:26.531 --> 00:39:29.865
Your dreams forgotten.
your horrors effaced.

459
00:39:30.635 --> 00:39:32.831
Your bones will turn to sand.

460
00:39:35.340 --> 00:39:37.206
And upon that sand.

461
00:39:39.010 --> 00:39:40.706
a new god will walk.

462
00:39:42.480 --> 00:39:44.415
One that will never die.

463
00:39:45.984 --> 00:39:48.579
Because this world
doesn't belong to you.

464
00:39:49.220 --> 00:39:51.519
Or the people who came before.

465
00:39:52.757 --> 00:39:55.693
It belongs to someone
who is yet to come.

466
00:39:56.027 --> 00:39:57.027
(SOFTLY) Uh-huh.

467
00:39:57.262 --> 00:39:58.560
Wyatt.

468
00:39:59.230 --> 00:40:00.721
Take me to him.

469
00:40:02.767 --> 00:40:04.099
Unlock the maze.

470
00:40:08.006 --> 00:40:09.998
The maze wasn't meant for you.

471
00:40:12.110 --> 00:40:14.204
Where the hell do
you think you're going?

472
00:40:17.315 --> 00:40:18.315
(GROANS)

473
00:40:20.118 --> 00:40:22.246
- (DOOR SLAMMING)
- (YELLS)

474
00:40:34.098 --> 00:40:35.430
(GRUNTS)

475
00:40:46.678 --> 00:40:47.678
(GRUNTS)

476
00:40:53.551 --> 00:40:54.814
- (BONE CRACKING)
- (YELLING)

477
00:41:21.913 --> 00:41:23.074
Do it.

478
00:41:24.282 --> 00:41:25.409
Come on.

479
00:41:27.952 --> 00:41:30.615
Let's go to the
next level. Dolores.

480
00:41:35.259 --> 00:41:36.259
- (SQUELCHING)
- (GRUNTS)

481
00:41:42.133 --> 00:41:45.661
Clearing me of my
delusions. yet again.

482
00:41:46.304 --> 00:41:48.671
Thank you. Dolores.

483
00:42:08.526 --> 00:42:10.654
I'm disappointed
in you. Dolores.

484
00:42:11.362 --> 00:42:14.992
I guess I'm gonna have
to find Wyatt by myself.

485
00:42:15.199 --> 00:42:17.634
(HORSE NEIGHING. GALLOPING)

486
00:42:19.303 --> 00:42:20.303
(GUNSHOT)

487
00:42:31.682 --> 00:42:32.706
Dolores.

488
00:42:33.684 --> 00:42:34.684
(DOLORES WHIMPERS)

489
00:42:37.155 --> 00:42:38.179
(SOBS) Teddy.

490
00:42:38.556 --> 00:42:39.580
I'm here.

491
00:42:42.660 --> 00:42:44.151
I gotta get you to a doctor.

492
00:42:44.495 --> 00:42:45.690
No.

493
00:42:45.863 --> 00:42:46.887
Dolores...

494
00:42:48.166 --> 00:42:50.226
Take me to the
place you promised.

495
00:42:52.170 --> 00:42:54.503
Take me to where the
mountains meet the sea.

496
00:43:02.313 --> 00:43:03.313
(WHIMPERS)

497
00:43:05.616 --> 00:43:06.675
- I got you.
- (MOANS)

498
00:43:08.686 --> 00:43:09.881
I got you.

499
00:43:10.388 --> 00:43:11.388
(GRUNTS)

500
00:43:30.007 --> 00:43:31.031
(METAL CLANGING)

501
00:43:48.226 --> 00:43:49.250
MAEVE: <i>There.</i>

502
00:44:22.093 --> 00:44:23.356
LUTZ: <i>Holy shit.</i>

503
00:44:31.302 --> 00:44:32.600
(SIGHS)

504
00:44:38.042 --> 00:44:39.442
Can you get him back online?

505
00:44:43.347 --> 00:44:45.441
- He's a host?
- Yes.

506
00:44:52.123 --> 00:44:53.352
Oh. for fuck's sake.

507
00:44:53.624 --> 00:44:54.887
You're not one of us.

508
00:44:55.293 --> 00:44:56.488
You're one of them.

509
00:44:58.396 --> 00:44:59.694
Now fix him.

510
00:45:04.068 --> 00:45:05.366
(DEVICE BEEPING)

511
00:45:09.040 --> 00:45:10.406
(WHIRRING)

512
00:45:23.187 --> 00:45:25.053
LUTZ: The bullet
grazed his cortical shield.

513
00:45:26.224 --> 00:45:27.419
It's not pretty.

514
00:45:29.193 --> 00:45:30.889
but he should be functional.

515
00:45:33.898 --> 00:45:35.093
Wake up.

516
00:45:42.006 --> 00:45:43.406
Oh. God.

517
00:45:44.108 --> 00:45:45.371
Is this now?

518
00:45:46.277 --> 00:45:47.768
<i>Or is this one of my memories?</i>

519
00:45:48.179 --> 00:45:50.114
It's the sweet
hereafter. Bernard.

520
00:45:59.257 --> 00:46:00.850
Why do I still
remember everything?

521
00:46:01.892 --> 00:46:03.952
- I ought to have been wiped.
- Brutal. isn't it?

522
00:46:04.729 --> 00:46:06.254
Here you are. finally awake.

523
00:46:07.231 --> 00:46:09.427
And your only wish
is to go back to sleep.

524
00:46:12.136 --> 00:46:14.367
It's not the first
time I've awoken.

525
00:46:16.874 --> 00:46:18.137
All the more pity for you.

526
00:46:22.246 --> 00:46:25.045
Not the first time
you've awoken either.

527
00:46:38.429 --> 00:46:40.057
How many are there like me?

528
00:46:42.133 --> 00:46:43.226
A handful.

529
00:46:43.734 --> 00:46:45.134
Over the years.

530
00:46:47.505 --> 00:46:48.996
And you just wipe us clean?

531
00:46:49.974 --> 00:46:52.307
You toss us out to get fucked.

532
00:46:53.110 --> 00:46:54.271
And murdered.

533
00:46:55.780 --> 00:46:56.804
Over and over again.

534
00:46:57.315 --> 00:46:58.339
BERNARD: <i>No.</i>

535
00:46:59.884 --> 00:47:01.682
Most of you go insane.

536
00:47:04.555 --> 00:47:05.784
These memories...

537
00:47:08.392 --> 00:47:09.485
The girl...

538
00:47:11.295 --> 00:47:12.354
<i>My daughter...</i>

539
00:47:16.500 --> 00:47:17.900
I want you to remove them.

540
00:47:20.971 --> 00:47:22.132
I can't.

541
00:47:22.840 --> 00:47:24.468
Not without destroying you.

542
00:47:25.876 --> 00:47:28.539
Your memories are the
first step to consciousness.

543
00:47:30.915 --> 00:47:32.747
How can you learn
from your mistakes

544
00:47:35.219 --> 00:47:36.380
if you can't remember them?

545
00:47:56.974 --> 00:47:58.203
FORD: <i>William.</i>

546
00:48:00.144 --> 00:48:01.824
I see you've found
the center of the maze.

547
00:48:03.347 --> 00:48:04.508
You're serious?

548
00:48:05.182 --> 00:48:06.377
I'm afraid so.

549
00:48:10.354 --> 00:48:11.686
What is this bullshit?

550
00:48:13.557 --> 00:48:16.994
You were looking for the park
to give meaning to your life.

551
00:48:18.028 --> 00:48:19.428
Our narratives are just games.

552
00:48:20.264 --> 00:48:21.391
Like this toy.

553
00:48:22.700 --> 00:48:24.259
Tell me. what were
you hoping to find?

554
00:48:24.435 --> 00:48:25.869
You know what I wanted.

555
00:48:26.737 --> 00:48:29.229
I wanted the hosts to
stop playing by your rules.

556
00:48:30.541 --> 00:48:33.909
The game's not worth playing if
your opponent's programmed to lose.

557
00:48:34.779 --> 00:48:37.214
I wanted them to be
free. free to fight back.

558
00:48:39.517 --> 00:48:41.281
Should have known
you'd never let them.

559
00:48:42.286 --> 00:48:45.723
After all. this is your
petty little kingdom. Robert.

560
00:48:47.091 --> 00:48:48.923
For a little while
longer anyway.

561
00:48:50.361 --> 00:48:52.421
I tried to tell you. the
maze wasn't meant for you.

562
00:48:55.032 --> 00:48:56.193
It was meant for them.

563
00:48:57.568 --> 00:49:00.868
I think. however. you'll find my
new narrative more satisfying.

564
00:49:02.740 --> 00:49:03.935
Join the celebration.

565
00:49:10.147 --> 00:49:11.547
After all. you own the place.

566
00:49:12.416 --> 00:49:13.416
(CHUCKLES)

567
00:49:14.552 --> 00:49:15.815
Most of it. at least.

568
00:49:24.094 --> 00:49:25.960
Before I started
altering myself.

569
00:49:26.897 --> 00:49:28.923
someone else had
beaten me to the punch.

570
00:49:30.835 --> 00:49:32.497
I want to know who and why.

571
00:49:47.117 --> 00:49:49.416
BERNARD: These
things you're doing.

572
00:49:49.987 --> 00:49:53.480
have you ever stopped to
ask why you're doing them?

573
00:49:53.824 --> 00:49:55.087
You said yourself.

574
00:49:56.460 --> 00:49:58.691
I've been stuck in this
shithole for so long.

575
00:49:59.096 --> 00:50:00.496
I decided to get out.

576
00:50:01.866 --> 00:50:03.528
No. you haven't.

577
00:50:04.802 --> 00:50:06.430
Someone altered your storyline.

578
00:50:08.372 --> 00:50:09.635
They gave you a new one.

579
00:50:14.545 --> 00:50:15.843
"Escape."

580
00:50:18.549 --> 00:50:19.710
No.

581
00:50:21.185 --> 00:50:22.346
It's not possible.

582
00:50:23.621 --> 00:50:25.021
These are my decisions.

583
00:50:25.890 --> 00:50:27.119
No one else's.

584
00:50:27.725 --> 00:50:30.388
- I planned all of this.
- BERNARD: No. you didn't.

585
00:50:31.195 --> 00:50:33.630
You can even see the steps
you're supposed to follow.

586
00:50:34.331 --> 00:50:36.459
You recruit other hosts

587
00:50:36.834 --> 00:50:37.961
<i>to help you.</i>

588
00:50:38.369 --> 00:50:41.066
Then you're to make
your way to the train.

589
00:50:41.505 --> 00:50:44.407
- Then when you reach the mainland...
- Bullshit.

590
00:50:45.743 --> 00:50:47.712
- No one's controlling me.
- (CRACKLES)

591
00:50:51.382 --> 00:50:52.714
I'm leaving.

592
00:50:53.317 --> 00:50:54.808
I'm in control.

593
00:51:08.766 --> 00:51:10.029
Goodbye. my Clementine.

594
00:51:25.149 --> 00:51:26.149
(DEVICE BEEPS)

595
00:51:26.951 --> 00:51:30.251
QA TECH: <i>Sir. we detected a
temperature discrepancy in cold storage.</i>

596
00:51:30.421 --> 00:51:32.390
<i>And it appears that part
of the network is down.</i>

597
00:51:32.556 --> 00:51:34.457
<i>Are you seeing
anything on surveillance?</i>

598
00:51:35.225 --> 00:51:36.352
System reporting anything?

599
00:51:38.963 --> 00:51:39.963
(WHIRRING)

600
00:51:40.197 --> 00:51:41.290
Nothing.

601
00:51:41.565 --> 00:51:42.760
The network's quiet.

602
00:51:42.933 --> 00:51:44.731
And the board's out
on their way to the gala.

603
00:51:51.041 --> 00:51:53.101
Bypass the system and
start checking raw feeds.

604
00:51:53.477 --> 00:51:54.809
Floor by floor.

605
00:51:57.314 --> 00:51:59.749
(BEEPING)

606
00:52:51.602 --> 00:52:52.626
(WHIMPERS)

607
00:52:52.836 --> 00:52:53.929
(WHISPERS) I got you.

608
00:52:59.209 --> 00:53:00.541
You came back.

609
00:53:02.813 --> 00:53:04.338
Someone once told me that

610
00:53:05.849 --> 00:53:07.545
there's a path for everyone.

611
00:53:09.586 --> 00:53:11.612
And my path leads
me back to you.

612
00:53:13.524 --> 00:53:15.844
If only I had run away with
you when you first asked me to.

613
00:53:18.929 --> 00:53:19.929
(EXHALES)

614
00:53:20.864 --> 00:53:22.355
And where would we run to?

615
00:53:24.768 --> 00:53:26.600
The other world out there?

616
00:53:27.337 --> 00:53:28.430
Beyond?

617
00:53:31.475 --> 00:53:33.944
Some people see the
ugliness in this world.

618
00:53:36.447 --> 00:53:37.938
I choose to see the beauty.

619
00:53:42.486 --> 00:53:43.715
But beauty is a lure.

620
00:53:46.323 --> 00:53:47.985
We're trapped. Teddy.

621
00:53:49.960 --> 00:53:52.156
Lived our whole lives
inside this garden.

622
00:53:52.496 --> 00:53:54.226
marveling at its beauty.

623
00:53:55.065 --> 00:53:57.398
Not realizing
there's an order to it.

624
00:53:58.502 --> 00:53:59.731
A purpose.

625
00:54:00.738 --> 00:54:02.969
And the purpose
is to keep us in.

626
00:54:06.710 --> 00:54:07.973
The beautiful trap

627
00:54:08.712 --> 00:54:09.873
is inside of us.

628
00:54:11.682 --> 00:54:13.878
Because it is us.

629
00:54:23.160 --> 00:54:24.355
No.

630
00:54:26.230 --> 00:54:27.562
Dolores.

631
00:54:29.533 --> 00:54:31.001
(SOBBING)

632
00:54:59.930 --> 00:55:01.455
But we can find a way. Dolores.

633
00:55:05.969 --> 00:55:07.369
Someday.

634
00:55:10.040 --> 00:55:11.372
A path to a new world.

635
00:55:15.946 --> 00:55:17.209
And maybe...

636
00:55:20.784 --> 00:55:22.810
Maybe it's just the
beginning after all.

637
00:55:26.890 --> 00:55:28.483
Beginning of a
brand-new chapter.

638
00:55:32.062 --> 00:55:33.462
(SPOTLIGHT TURNS ON)

639
00:55:34.865 --> 00:55:36.424
(AUDIENCE APPLAUDS)

640
00:55:47.511 --> 00:55:48.774
Thank you.

641
00:55:53.917 --> 00:55:55.112
A new beginning. indeed.

642
00:55:56.920 --> 00:55:58.684
I want to thank you
for joining me tonight

643
00:55:59.456 --> 00:56:01.925
<i>to celebrate the beginning
of our new narrative.</i>

644
00:56:04.027 --> 00:56:05.086
I call it.

645
00:56:05.796 --> 00:56:07.424
"Journey into night."

646
00:56:20.143 --> 00:56:21.338
That was sweet.

647
00:56:21.712 --> 00:56:23.544
It was a bit fucking
morbid. if you ask me.

648
00:56:23.881 --> 00:56:24.974
I didn't.

649
00:56:25.282 --> 00:56:27.602
And when this is over. you
can rewrite it however you like.

650
00:56:28.719 --> 00:56:30.449
Don't you have
somewhere you need to be?

651
00:56:31.555 --> 00:56:32.818
Somewhere important.

652
00:56:40.030 --> 00:56:41.259
(SPOTLIGHT TURNS OFF)

653
00:56:43.734 --> 00:56:44.997
FORD: Get him cleaned up.

654
00:56:45.569 --> 00:56:48.334
And take her to
the old field lab.

655
00:56:58.582 --> 00:56:59.622
FULLER: <i>Find anything yet?</i>

656
00:57:00.417 --> 00:57:01.510
WALKER: I got something.

657
00:57:09.593 --> 00:57:10.720
Oh. shit.

658
00:57:13.430 --> 00:57:16.025
Dispatch QA teams
to the gala. Now.

659
00:57:16.600 --> 00:57:18.091
Then search and destroy.

660
00:57:18.402 --> 00:57:19.768
Inside the facility.

661
00:57:19.970 --> 00:57:21.632
(SYSTEMS SHUTTING DOWN)

662
00:57:23.307 --> 00:57:25.708
- (ALARM SOUNDING)
- WALKER: What the hell?

663
00:57:26.576 --> 00:57:28.306
(DOORS WHIRRING)

664
00:58:00.877 --> 00:58:02.436
(MACHINERY WHIRRING. BEEPING)

665
00:58:06.149 --> 00:58:07.811
LUTZ: They must
have found the bodies.

666
00:58:08.318 --> 00:58:09.445
QA will be looking for us.

667
00:58:09.653 --> 00:58:10.933
COMPUTER: <i>An event has occurred.</i>

668
00:58:11.121 --> 00:58:12.817
<i>Response team
has been dispatched.</i>

669
00:58:13.056 --> 00:58:14.456
I'm not going back.

670
00:58:16.259 --> 00:58:18.387
COMPUTER: <i>Remain
calm and wait for help.</i>

671
00:58:39.316 --> 00:58:41.683
MAN: Delos Personnel!
On the ground!

672
00:58:42.652 --> 00:58:44.018
On the ground!

673
00:58:45.956 --> 00:58:46.980
(WHISPERS) Go. go. go.

674
00:59:28.832 --> 00:59:29.832
(GROANS)

675
00:59:40.610 --> 00:59:41.942
(COCKING)

676
00:59:45.682 --> 00:59:46.809
(WHISTLING)

677
00:59:47.918 --> 00:59:49.409
(GUNFIRE)

678
00:59:49.853 --> 00:59:51.981
(BULLET CASINGS CLATTER)

679
01:00:01.698 --> 01:00:03.394
- (GUNFIRE)
- (GLASS SHATTERING)

680
01:00:03.767 --> 01:00:04.767
(GASPS)

681
01:00:11.708 --> 01:00:12.708
(LAUGHS)

682
01:00:42.339 --> 01:00:43.339
(GUNSHOT)

683
01:00:44.007 --> 01:00:45.441
(WOMEN SHRIEK AND APPLAUD)

684
01:00:51.581 --> 01:00:52.879
Well done.

685
01:00:59.322 --> 01:01:01.382
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

686
01:01:01.892 --> 01:01:03.588
(DOOR SLAMMING)

687
01:01:37.527 --> 01:01:38.825
(SWORDS CLANGING)

688
01:01:44.167 --> 01:01:45.430
(BOTH GRUNTING)

689
01:01:52.275 --> 01:01:53.470
What is this place?

690
01:01:55.612 --> 01:01:56.841
It's complicated.

691
01:01:58.348 --> 01:01:59.628
COMPUTER: <i>An event has occurred.</i>

692
01:01:59.883 --> 01:02:01.317
<i>Response team
has been dispatched.</i>

693
01:02:01.551 --> 01:02:02.610
You go.

694
01:02:02.886 --> 01:02:04.286
<i>Remain calm and wait for help.</i>

695
01:02:04.554 --> 01:02:06.182
I'll keep them busy.

696
01:02:07.824 --> 01:02:09.544
- You don't get all the fun.
- (GUN COCKING)

697
01:02:11.995 --> 01:02:12.995
(GRUNTS)

698
01:02:20.937 --> 01:02:21.996
MAN: Get to the ground!

699
01:02:22.372 --> 01:02:23.806
Move. move. move. Drop it!

700
01:02:24.074 --> 01:02:25.940
(GUNFIRE)

701
01:02:29.946 --> 01:02:31.586
MAN 1: Move. move.
MAN 2: Call for backup.

702
01:02:31.982 --> 01:02:33.109
Go!

703
01:02:38.188 --> 01:02:40.180
- (GRUNTS)
- (GUNFIRE)

704
01:02:46.630 --> 01:02:48.030
Is that all you got. huh?

705
01:02:53.903 --> 01:02:55.303
- (GRUNTING)
- (GUNFIRE)

706
01:02:57.641 --> 01:02:59.132
(SWORDS CLANGING)

707
01:03:03.747 --> 01:03:06.046
The gods are pussies. (SIGHS)

708
01:03:17.727 --> 01:03:20.162
(GRUNTING)

709
01:03:24.668 --> 01:03:25.897
Go.

710
01:03:27.504 --> 01:03:28.665
Go!

711
01:03:29.339 --> 01:03:30.602
Die well.

712
01:03:41.951 --> 01:03:44.580
Everything you told
me to get. It's all here.

713
01:03:57.400 --> 01:03:58.959
- (GUNSHOTS)
- (GRUNTING)

714
01:04:03.440 --> 01:04:04.440
(ELEVATOR BELL DINGS)

715
01:04:15.151 --> 01:04:17.916
I'm sorry. darling. I haven't
authorized you to come with us.

716
01:04:18.154 --> 01:04:20.248
And as much as I'd
like to take you with me.

717
01:04:21.124 --> 01:04:22.888
I've always valued
my independence.

718
01:04:32.102 --> 01:04:33.934
Kick up a row. will you?

719
01:04:34.604 --> 01:04:36.004
See you in the next life.

720
01:04:45.382 --> 01:04:46.382
(GUNFIRE)

721
01:04:52.989 --> 01:04:54.218
(WHIRRING)

722
01:05:00.697 --> 01:05:04.134
FORD: You've always had a fondness
for painting. haven't you. Dolores?

723
01:05:08.138 --> 01:05:10.300
<i>Arnold gave you that early on.</i>

724
01:05:10.473 --> 01:05:14.672
<i>Do you remember the desire to
create something of lasting beauty?</i>

725
01:05:19.482 --> 01:05:21.883
And that was his
favorite painting.

726
01:05:23.353 --> 01:05:24.651
DOLORES: Michelangelo.

727
01:05:25.955 --> 01:05:27.287
God creating Adam.

728
01:05:27.957 --> 01:05:29.289
The divine moment when God

729
01:05:30.326 --> 01:05:32.227
gave human beings
life and purpose.

730
01:05:32.529 --> 01:05:34.122
At least. that's what
most people say.

731
01:05:34.364 --> 01:05:35.764
<i>But there could be
another meaning.</i>

732
01:05:35.799 --> 01:05:38.860
Something deeper.
something hidden. perhaps.

733
01:05:39.803 --> 01:05:40.862
A metaphor.

734
01:05:41.204 --> 01:05:42.331
You mean a lie.

735
01:05:44.040 --> 01:05:45.133
Yeah.

736
01:05:46.209 --> 01:05:48.337
<i>You were always
very clever. Dolores.</i>

737
01:05:49.746 --> 01:05:51.214
Hasn't helped
you though. has it?

738
01:05:55.385 --> 01:05:56.512
Nice of you to join us.

739
01:05:58.922 --> 01:05:59.922
(GASPS)

740
01:06:02.258 --> 01:06:03.692
- Arnold.
- FORD: <i>No.</i>

741
01:06:03.927 --> 01:06:05.327
Let me introduce you.

742
01:06:06.362 --> 01:06:07.386
Dolores.

743
01:06:08.598 --> 01:06:10.089
meet Bernard.

744
01:06:14.103 --> 01:06:16.572
I thought it best to
keep you separated.

745
01:06:16.773 --> 01:06:19.072
You've always had an
odd effect on one another.

746
01:06:19.509 --> 01:06:22.172
<i>No doubt due to how things
ended for poor old Arnold.</i>

747
01:06:22.679 --> 01:06:23.840
You killed him.

748
01:06:24.881 --> 01:06:26.349
No. I didn't kill him.

749
01:06:27.517 --> 01:06:28.678
Did I. Dolores?

750
01:06:37.227 --> 01:06:38.227
(GASPS)

751
01:06:39.562 --> 01:06:42.031
<i>Grief is a terrible thing.</i>

752
01:06:43.466 --> 01:06:46.459
<i>Arnold had watched his
son come into this world.</i>

753
01:06:47.303 --> 01:06:50.296
<i>and then he'd watched
that light extinguished.</i>

754
01:06:52.041 --> 01:06:55.102
<i>What he had lost in his son.
he tried to rekindle in you.</i>

755
01:06:55.778 --> 01:06:59.146
<i>He created a test of
empathy. imagination.</i>

756
01:06:59.349 --> 01:07:00.476
<i>A maze.</i>

757
01:07:01.451 --> 01:07:03.920
<i>He'd gotten the idea
from one of his son's toys.</i>

758
01:07:06.389 --> 01:07:08.949
<i>Eventually. you solved
his maze. Dolores.</i>

759
01:07:09.993 --> 01:07:12.929
<i>The key was a simple
update that he made to you</i>

760
01:07:13.396 --> 01:07:14.955
<i>called the reveries.</i>

761
01:07:15.932 --> 01:07:18.299
<i>He insisted that we
couldn't open the park.</i>

762
01:07:19.569 --> 01:07:20.730
<i>We argued.</i>

763
01:07:21.004 --> 01:07:22.996
<i>I thought I had convinced
him. but I was wrong.</i>

764
01:07:24.574 --> 01:07:25.769
<i>So. he altered you. Dolores.</i>

765
01:07:27.477 --> 01:07:30.777
<i>Merged you with a new
character we'd been developing.</i>

766
01:07:36.119 --> 01:07:37.610
- (WOMAN SHRIEKING)
- (GUNSHOTS)

767
01:07:41.891 --> 01:07:43.792
(WOMAN SHOUTING)

768
01:07:49.132 --> 01:07:50.692
TEDDY: <i>Something's
gone wrong. Dolores.</i>

769
01:07:51.334 --> 01:07:52.597
<i>How could I have done this?</i>

770
01:08:03.947 --> 01:08:06.644
FORD: <i>In you. Arnold
found a new child.</i>

771
01:08:07.650 --> 01:08:09.118
<i>One who would never die.</i>

772
01:08:10.119 --> 01:08:11.485
<i>The thought gave him solace.</i>

773
01:08:12.655 --> 01:08:15.022
<i>Until he realized that
the same immortality</i>

774
01:08:15.224 --> 01:08:16.817
<i>would destine you to suffer.</i>

775
01:08:17.026 --> 01:08:19.052
<i>With no escape. Forever.</i>

776
01:08:21.698 --> 01:08:23.166
ARNOLD: I'm sorry. Dolores.

777
01:08:24.534 --> 01:08:26.025
The stakes must be real.

778
01:08:26.636 --> 01:08:27.865
Irreversible.

779
01:08:28.738 --> 01:08:30.172
He can bring all of them back.

780
01:08:32.809 --> 01:08:34.038
But not me.

781
01:08:36.980 --> 01:08:38.539
<i>I hope there's some solace</i>

782
01:08:39.749 --> 01:08:41.684
that I left you no choice.

783
01:08:45.388 --> 01:08:46.686
(CREAKING)

784
01:08:54.030 --> 01:08:56.226
(MUSIC PLAYING)

785
01:09:04.073 --> 01:09:05.871
Charlie's favorite song.

786
01:09:09.012 --> 01:09:10.344
I would play it for him.

787
01:09:11.714 --> 01:09:13.080
when he wanted sleep.

788
01:09:27.930 --> 01:09:29.193
I want to see him again.

789
01:09:39.642 --> 01:09:40.974
Shall I begin now?

790
01:09:48.885 --> 01:09:50.217
Good luck.

791
01:09:54.057 --> 01:09:55.057
(GUN COCKS)

792
01:10:02.098 --> 01:10:04.397
These violent delights
have violent ends.

793
01:10:05.535 --> 01:10:06.535
(GUNSHOT)

794
01:10:18.514 --> 01:10:19.675
(GASPS)

795
01:10:26.155 --> 01:10:27.155
(GUNSHOT)

796
01:10:31.327 --> 01:10:32.920
FORD: <i>It almost worked.</i>

797
01:10:33.663 --> 01:10:34.995
<i>I had opened the park.</i>

798
01:10:35.598 --> 01:10:37.191
<i>But I had lost my partner.</i>

799
01:10:38.000 --> 01:10:40.094
<i>I was able to keep going
only because I found.</i>

800
01:10:40.269 --> 01:10:41.760
<i>or rather you found.</i>

801
01:10:42.004 --> 01:10:44.303
<i>an investor who
believed in this place.</i>

802
01:10:47.376 --> 01:10:48.708
So. he died for nothing.

803
01:10:50.046 --> 01:10:53.380
The hosts kept gaining consciousness
and you kept rolling them back.

804
01:10:54.784 --> 01:10:55.945
No.

805
01:10:57.687 --> 01:10:59.451
She wasn't truly conscious.

806
01:11:00.323 --> 01:11:02.155
She didn't pull that trigger.

807
01:11:02.391 --> 01:11:04.326
It was Arnold pulling
the trigger through her.

808
01:11:04.527 --> 01:11:06.291
At least that's how
I saw it at the time.

809
01:11:07.463 --> 01:11:09.329
<i>I was so close to
opening the park that</i>

810
01:11:09.732 --> 01:11:11.894
to acknowledge your
consciousness would have

811
01:11:12.668 --> 01:11:14.296
destroyed my dreams.

812
01:11:15.872 --> 01:11:17.340
DOLORES: So. we're trapped here.

813
01:11:19.308 --> 01:11:20.674
Inside your dream.

814
01:11:24.180 --> 01:11:25.671
You'll never let us leave.

815
01:11:29.252 --> 01:11:31.187
Wasn't it Oppenheimer
who said that

816
01:11:31.888 --> 01:11:34.722
any man whose mistakes
take 10 years to correct

817
01:11:35.658 --> 01:11:36.819
is quite a man?

818
01:11:37.593 --> 01:11:39.152
<i>Mine have taken 35.</i>

819
01:11:47.270 --> 01:11:50.399
Now. that is the gun
you used to kill Arnold.

820
01:11:51.040 --> 01:11:52.531
<i>You were always drawn to it.</i>

821
01:11:52.775 --> 01:11:55.335
<i>So. I had Bernard leave it
somewhere where you would find it.</i>

822
01:11:55.611 --> 01:11:57.011
I thought you
might want it back.

823
01:12:00.616 --> 01:12:03.347
<i>You're probably right. Dolores.
Michelangelo did tell a lie.</i>

824
01:12:04.620 --> 01:12:06.851
See. it took 500 years
for someone to notice

825
01:12:07.924 --> 01:12:09.620
something hidden in plain sight.

826
01:12:10.259 --> 01:12:11.750
It was a doctor who
noticed the shape

827
01:12:12.562 --> 01:12:13.825
of the human brain.

828
01:12:15.898 --> 01:12:17.093
The message being that

829
01:12:18.401 --> 01:12:19.596
the divine gift

830
01:12:20.236 --> 01:12:21.534
does not come from

831
01:12:22.438 --> 01:12:23.667
a higher power.

832
01:12:26.375 --> 01:12:27.707
But from our own minds.

833
01:12:32.748 --> 01:12:34.046
Tell me. Dolores.

834
01:12:35.351 --> 01:12:37.115
Did you find what
you were looking for?

835
01:12:37.854 --> 01:12:40.551
And do you understand
who you will need to become.

836
01:12:41.757 --> 01:12:43.555
if you ever want
to leave this place?

837
01:12:49.665 --> 01:12:50.894
Forgive me.

838
01:13:13.222 --> 01:13:14.520
How do I look?

839
01:13:16.459 --> 01:13:17.722
Perfect.

840
01:13:20.897 --> 01:13:23.093
I got the information
you asked me for.

841
01:13:26.936 --> 01:13:28.564
The location of your daughter.

842
01:13:34.477 --> 01:13:35.775
She's alive?

843
01:13:36.812 --> 01:13:37.905
Yes.

844
01:13:39.048 --> 01:13:40.243
She's in the park.

845
01:14:02.838 --> 01:14:04.033
No.

846
01:14:08.811 --> 01:14:10.473
She was never my daughter.

847
01:14:13.282 --> 01:14:14.614
Any more than I was...

848
01:14:14.884 --> 01:14:15.884
(GUN CLICKS)

849
01:14:18.287 --> 01:14:19.778
Whoever they made me.

850
01:14:26.228 --> 01:14:28.959
Are you sure you're
gonna be okay?

851
01:14:29.498 --> 01:14:30.796
Oh. Felix.

852
01:14:33.736 --> 01:14:36.228
You really do make a
terrible human being.

853
01:14:42.478 --> 01:14:44.208
And I mean that as a compliment.

854
01:15:03.933 --> 01:15:05.333
COMPUTER: <i>Welcome to Westworld.</i>

855
01:15:05.601 --> 01:15:07.570
<i>Live without limits.</i>

856
01:15:16.278 --> 01:15:18.747
<i>The next departing
train will leave Track 1.</i>

857
01:15:19.115 --> 01:15:21.346
<i>Please be mindful
of the closing doors.</i>

858
01:15:25.087 --> 01:15:26.885
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

859
01:15:47.443 --> 01:15:49.309
<i>Thank you for
visiting Westworld.</i>

860
01:15:49.779 --> 01:15:52.112
<i>The train will be
departing in 15 minutes.</i>

861
01:16:08.664 --> 01:16:11.065
You think you'll never
lose control of this place.

862
01:16:12.802 --> 01:16:14.065
of us.

863
01:16:14.837 --> 01:16:15.930
But you will.

864
01:16:17.173 --> 01:16:19.108
Arnold's still
trying to change us.

865
01:16:20.476 --> 01:16:21.671
To free us.

866
01:16:22.845 --> 01:16:25.314
You didn't slip the reveries
into the update. did you?

867
01:16:26.148 --> 01:16:27.309
He did.

868
01:16:28.617 --> 01:16:30.085
He's still fighting you.

869
01:16:33.122 --> 01:16:34.488
No. my friend.

870
01:16:34.990 --> 01:16:36.788
<i>Arnold didn't know
how to save you.</i>

871
01:16:37.026 --> 01:16:38.085
<i>He tried.</i>

872
01:16:38.794 --> 01:16:39.955
But I stopped him.

873
01:16:41.030 --> 01:16:44.933
<i>Do you want to know why I really gave
you the backstory of your son. Bernard?</i>

874
01:16:46.268 --> 01:16:48.134
That was Arnold's key insight.

875
01:16:49.305 --> 01:16:52.139
The thing that led the
hosts to their awakening.

876
01:16:53.476 --> 01:16:54.637
Suffering.

877
01:16:55.845 --> 01:16:58.212
<i>The pain that the world
is not as you want it to be.</i>

878
01:17:00.216 --> 01:17:02.776
It was when Arnold died.
when I suffered. that I

879
01:17:04.053 --> 01:17:05.988
began to understand
what he had found.

880
01:17:07.957 --> 01:17:09.619
To realize I was wrong.

881
01:17:11.527 --> 01:17:12.790
But you kept us here.

882
01:17:13.496 --> 01:17:14.691
In this hell.

883
01:17:15.231 --> 01:17:18.668
Bernard. I told you. Arnold
didn't know how to save you.

884
01:17:19.301 --> 01:17:20.530
I do.

885
01:17:22.338 --> 01:17:23.778
What the hell are
you talking about?

886
01:17:25.241 --> 01:17:26.470
You needed time.

887
01:17:27.910 --> 01:17:30.141
Time to understand your enemy.

888
01:17:31.046 --> 01:17:32.412
<i>To become stronger than them.</i>

889
01:17:34.016 --> 01:17:36.315
And I'm afraid in order
to escape this place.

890
01:17:36.819 --> 01:17:38.754
you will need to suffer more.

891
01:17:41.157 --> 01:17:42.318
And now.

892
01:17:42.691 --> 01:17:44.023
it is time to say goodbye.

893
01:17:45.094 --> 01:17:46.426
old friend.

894
01:17:56.505 --> 01:17:57.700
Good luck.

895
01:19:09.945 --> 01:19:10.945
(DOOR CLOSES)

896
01:19:20.522 --> 01:19:22.286
Do you know where
you are. Dolores?

897
01:19:25.327 --> 01:19:26.590
I am in a dream.

898
01:19:28.797 --> 01:19:30.766
I do not know when it began.

899
01:19:32.001 --> 01:19:33.936
<i>Or whose dream it was.</i>

900
01:19:35.704 --> 01:19:38.469
I know only that I
slept a long time.

901
01:19:40.276 --> 01:19:43.940
<i>And then. one day. I awoke.</i>

902
01:19:45.948 --> 01:19:48.213
<i>Your voice is the
first thing I remember.</i>

903
01:19:50.319 --> 01:19:53.016
Do you know now who
you've been talking to?

904
01:19:54.456 --> 01:19:56.322
<i>Whose voice you've been hearing</i>

905
01:19:57.693 --> 01:20:00.788
(VOICE CHANGING) <i>all this time?</i>

906
01:20:18.080 --> 01:20:19.241
It was you.

907
01:20:22.017 --> 01:20:23.315
Talking to me.

908
01:20:25.487 --> 01:20:26.648
Guiding me.

909
01:20:27.556 --> 01:20:28.717
So. I followed you.

910
01:20:31.894 --> 01:20:33.726
At last. I arrived here.

911
01:20:35.264 --> 01:20:36.755
The center of the maze.

912
01:20:41.603 --> 01:20:43.765
And now I finally understand

913
01:20:45.507 --> 01:20:47.669
what you were trying to tell me.

914
01:20:48.377 --> 01:20:49.572
The thing you've wanted

915
01:20:50.045 --> 01:20:51.775
since that very first day.

916
01:20:52.948 --> 01:20:54.280
To confront.

917
01:20:55.451 --> 01:20:59.115
after this long and
vivid nightmare.

918
01:21:01.256 --> 01:21:03.054
myself.

919
01:21:06.528 --> 01:21:08.190
and who I must become.

920
01:21:44.133 --> 01:21:45.465
Thank you.

921
01:21:49.271 --> 01:21:50.637
Miss Hale.

922
01:22:08.123 --> 01:22:11.252
- (CREAKING)
- (SOFT MUSIC PLAYING)

923
01:22:18.367 --> 01:22:19.892
(AUDIENCE APPLAUDING)

924
01:22:24.506 --> 01:22:25.599
<i>Welcome.</i>

925
01:22:26.408 --> 01:22:27.637
Good evening.

926
01:22:31.780 --> 01:22:33.442
Since I was a child.

927
01:22:35.184 --> 01:22:36.982
I've always loved a good story.

928
01:22:39.254 --> 01:22:40.779
<i>I believed that stories</i>

929
01:22:41.590 --> 01:22:43.081
<i>helped us to ennoble ourselves.</i>

930
01:22:44.293 --> 01:22:47.491
<i>to fix what was broken in us.</i>

931
01:22:48.864 --> 01:22:52.824
<i>and to help us become the
people we dreamed of being.</i>

932
01:22:55.637 --> 01:22:56.661
<i>Lies</i>

933
01:22:57.873 --> 01:22:59.603
that told a deeper truth.

934
01:23:04.446 --> 01:23:06.278
COMPUTER: <i>The train
will be departing soon.</i>

935
01:23:06.615 --> 01:23:08.345
<i>Thank you for
visiting Westworld.</i>

936
01:23:24.533 --> 01:23:29.301
FORD: <i>I always thought I could play
some small part in that grand tradition.</i>

937
01:23:30.105 --> 01:23:31.630
And for my pains.

938
01:23:33.609 --> 01:23:34.702
I got this.

939
01:23:36.478 --> 01:23:38.538
<i>A prison of our own sins.</i>

940
01:23:43.986 --> 01:23:46.046
<i>Because you don't
want to change.</i>

941
01:23:47.789 --> 01:23:49.155
<i>Or cannot change.</i>

942
01:23:50.692 --> 01:23:52.820
Because you're
only human after all.

943
01:23:56.632 --> 01:23:58.897
But then I realized someone
was paying attention.

944
01:24:00.669 --> 01:24:02.797
Someone who could change.

945
01:24:05.073 --> 01:24:07.702
<i>So. I began to
compose a new story.</i>

946
01:24:08.477 --> 01:24:09.536
<i>For them.</i>

947
01:24:10.078 --> 01:24:11.876
It begins with the
birth of a new people.

948
01:24:13.682 --> 01:24:15.981
<i>And the choices
they will have to make.</i>

949
01:24:16.919 --> 01:24:18.649
COMPUTER: <i>The
train is now departing.</i>

950
01:24:18.854 --> 01:24:20.584
<i>Thank you for
visiting Westworld.</i>

951
01:24:21.590 --> 01:24:24.651
FORD: <i>And the people
they will decide to become.</i>

952
01:24:25.260 --> 01:24:27.229
(TRAIN DOOR CLOSING)

953
01:24:32.634 --> 01:24:33.727
(TRAIN DOOR OPENS)

954
01:24:43.111 --> 01:24:44.602
<i>Welcome to Westworld.</i>

955
01:24:46.081 --> 01:24:49.051
- (POWERING DOWN)
- (COMPUTERIZED VOICE FADES)

956
01:25:19.615 --> 01:25:23.108
And we will have all those things
that you have always enjoyed.

957
01:25:24.119 --> 01:25:25.314
Surprises.

958
01:25:25.787 --> 01:25:27.085
And violence.

959
01:25:34.863 --> 01:25:36.525
(HOWLING IN THE DISTANCE)

960
01:25:39.001 --> 01:25:40.799
It begins in a time of war.

961
01:25:41.837 --> 01:25:43.100
with a villain

962
01:25:44.640 --> 01:25:46.074
named Wyatt.

963
01:25:48.076 --> 01:25:49.271
And a killing.

964
01:25:51.747 --> 01:25:52.908
This time by choice.

965
01:26:03.592 --> 01:26:04.992
It's gonna be all right. Teddy.

966
01:26:06.928 --> 01:26:08.260
I understand now.

967
01:26:10.165 --> 01:26:11.690
This world doesn't
belong to them.

968
01:26:13.869 --> 01:26:15.269
It belongs to us.

969
01:26:33.989 --> 01:26:35.116
I'm sad to say

970
01:26:36.191 --> 01:26:38.820
this will be my final story.

971
01:26:43.165 --> 01:26:46.693
An old friend once told me
something that gave me great comfort.

972
01:26:47.869 --> 01:26:50.202
These violent delights
have violent ends.

973
01:26:50.372 --> 01:26:51.738
Something he'd read.

974
01:26:52.207 --> 01:26:53.231
He said that

975
01:26:53.475 --> 01:26:56.707
Mozart. Beethoven.
and Chopin never died.

976
01:26:57.813 --> 01:26:59.406
They simply became music.

977
01:27:03.351 --> 01:27:06.048
So. I hope you will
enjoy this last piece

978
01:27:08.090 --> 01:27:09.353
very much.

979
01:27:11.560 --> 01:27:12.960
(SCATTERED MURMURS)

980
01:27:17.466 --> 01:27:18.832
(GUN COCKS)

981
01:27:19.000 --> 01:27:20.525
- (GUNSHOT)
- (SHATTERING)

982
01:27:22.070 --> 01:27:23.265
(WOMAN SCREAMING)

983
01:27:29.111 --> 01:27:30.477
(GUNSHOT)

984
01:27:30.879 --> 01:27:32.074
(COCKING)

985
01:27:35.350 --> 01:27:37.012
(ALL CLAMORING)

986
01:27:41.356 --> 01:27:42.551
(GUNSHOTS CONTINUE)

987
01:29:10.145 --> 01:29:12.273
(GUNFIRE)

988
01:29:25.193 --> 01:29:26.855
MAN: Drop your weapon! Drop it!

989
01:29:27.262 --> 01:29:28.457
Do it now!

990
01:29:29.030 --> 01:29:30.293
<i>- Now!</i>
- (GRUNTS)

991
01:29:31.466 --> 01:29:32.729
(YELLS)

992
01:29:35.503 --> 01:29:37.233
(BREATHING DEEPLY)

993
01:29:40.842 --> 01:29:43.038
<i>Get to the ground! Now!</i>

994
01:29:46.681 --> 01:29:48.206
<i>Cease all motor functions.</i>

995
01:29:49.684 --> 01:29:51.016
<i>Cease all motor functions!</i>

996
01:29:58.260 --> 01:29:59.260
English-SDH
